data.title: Assembly - Char-Broil TRU-Infrared Big Easy 2-in-1 Electric Smoker & Roaster
data.description:
Assembly Of The Char-Broil TRU-Infrared Big Easy 2-in-1 Electric Smoker Roaster

You will find that most of the product assembly has been completed for you at the factory. Complete any remaining steps and reference all safety and usage information found in the Product Guide. 

Be sure the holes in the cooking chamber are positioned towards the front of the unit. This will align the holes in the cooking chamber with the holes in the smoker box so that smoke flows properly during use.

data.title: How is an Infrared Grill Different
data.description:
The Char-Broil® TRU-Infrared™ Difference:

The science behind TRU-Infrared tells a juicy story. Unlike traditional gas grills that use convective heat (hot air) to cook food, Char-Broil's TRU-Infrared grills limit the hot air flow and use natural, radiant heat to cook food directly without drying. While convective heat destroys food's moisture barrier, infrared heat penetrates it without drying, locking in natural juices and flavors.

data.title: How to Grill Filet Mignon
data.description:
Chef Enrique offers grilling tips using a Char-Broil TRU-Infrared Performance Grill.

In this episode we learn how to grill a filet mignon with veggies. Some of the tips the Chef includes are:
- Brush the meat with olive oil before grill
- Grill on high heat to seal in the juices
